[1.775, "o", "\u001b[1mcoop\u001b[0m v3.0.0 — run a coding agent all night long in a box it can't escape.\r\nUsage: coop <command> [args]\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mAGENTS\u001b[0m\r\n  coop claude|codex|gemini [args]   a sandboxed agent (its autonomous flags + your args)\r\n  coop fusion [agent]               a council: one agent leads, the others advise, it synthesizes\r\n  coop run -- <cmd...>              run a raw command in the box\r\n  coop shell                        an interactive shell in the box\r\n  coop login <agent> [--profile p]  authenticate an agent (a profile = one subscription)\r\n  coop profiles [agent]             list stored credential profiles and which are signed in\r\n  coop acp [agent|fusion]           serve as an ACP agent over stdio (for editors like Zed)\r\n  coop <agent> --consult            add a read-only second opinion from the other agents on a hard call\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mFORKS — review and land work like a PR\u001b[0m\r\n  coop fork <name> [agent]          open or re-enter a fork and run an agent\r\n  coop fork ls                      list this repo's forks\r\n  coop fork review <name>           show a fork's brief + diff\r\n  coop fork merge <name>            rebase the fork onto your branch and land it\r\n  coop fork logs [name]             tail a fork's loop log (no name: every fork)\r\n  coop fork rm <name>               discard a fork\r\n  coop fork stop <name>             stop a detached loop\r\n  coop fork open <name>             open the fork in your editor\r\n  coop fork path <name>             print the fork's filesystem path\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mUNATTENDED\u001b[0m\r\n  coop loop [agent] [--tasks p]…    work the queue(s) until done, then audit\r\n  coop pool add|rm|clear            pick which subscriptions the loop rotates on a rate limit\r\n  coop fleet init|up|down|split|watch|prune  drive a fleet of forks from .agent/fleet\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mTASKS — a folder-per-task queue in .agent/tasks/\u001b[0m\r\n  coop tasks ls                     show the queue, grouped by state\r\n  coop tasks watch                  live board: the queue + any active forks, deduped (auto-exits when done)\r\n  coop tasks add \"<title>\"          add a task; claim/block/unblock/done move it through its states\r\n  coop tasks decisions              show what's blocked on a human decision (-i to answer them)\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mSETUP & MAINTENANCE\u001b[0m\r\n  coop init [--stack asdf]          scaffold the queue, hooks, and skills\r\n  coop build                        build the box image (stable, pinned)\r\n  coop update                       self-update coop, then rebuild the box image fresh (latest base + agents)\r\n  \u001b[2mcoop up                           start sibling services (none in compose.agent.yml yet)\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2mcoop down                         stop sibling services\u001b[0m\r\n  coop doctor                       prove isolation — attack the box, check it holds\r\n  coop check-secrets                scan the working tree for committed secrets\r\n  coop help                         this help\r\n  coop version                      print the version\r\n\r\nRun 'coop help <command>' or 'coop <command> --help' for a command's details —\r\nfor an agent (claude/codex/gemini), --help is the agent's own.\r\n\r\nConfig  ~/.config/coop/coop.conf, or COOP_* env vars\r\nAuth    ~/.config/coop/agents\r\nDocs    https://github.com/AndrewDryga/coop\r\n"]
